<title type="html"><![CDATA[How does Action Replay/Game Shark work for CDROM consoles?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2922&amp;p=21792#p21792"><![CDATA[
Yes, the AR master code installs a kernel into some unused area of RAM that gets called each vblank. Interestingly enough, the ARDS code format almost matches that of DipStar, a cheating program from the DS homebrew scene created before Datel figured out how to make ARDS.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Feb 01, 2007 6:07 pm</p><hr />
